Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven to 400 degrees. Soak the
@wooden skewers{12} in water. Cut the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into
large wedges like steak fries. Toss the potato wedges on a #baking sheet
with @olive oil{2%tablespoons} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.
Place in the oven for ~{25%minutes}, turning once, until golden brown.

In a #medium bowl{}, stir together the @whole grain mustard{2%tablespoon}
and @honey{2%jar}. Set ¼ of the mixture aside in a #small bowl{}. Cut the
@chicken thighs{24%ounce} into bite-sized pieces, and toss into the medium
bowl with the marinade. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: If you have the time, marinate the chicken, covered, for up to 24 hours
> in the fridge.

Prep the salad: Trim and thinly slice the @baby gem lettuce{2}. Core, seed,
and dice the @Roma tomato{2}. Place them into a #large bowl{}.

Thread the chicken onto skewers. Place the skewers onto a lightly oiled
baking sheet. Bake ~{10-15%minutes}, until cooked through. Remove the potato
wedges from the oven, then heat broiler to high (or oven to 500 degrees).
Broil the skewers another ~{3-5%minutes}, until slightly charred.

Finish and plate: Toss the salad with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Serve the chicken skewers on a bed of
salad with the potato wedges on the side. Drizzle the reserved marinade over
the chicken skewers, and serve with the @sour cream{4%tablespoon} for
dipping. Enjoy!